521
00:53:36,363 --> 00:53:39,196
Joseph, please,
sit down.

522
00:53:39,266 --> 00:53:43,362
I'm afraid if I sit down,
I'm never gonna get up again.

523
00:53:47,574 --> 00:53:49,508
Years ago...

524
00:53:49,576 --> 00:53:52,044
when I was first
on the force,

525
00:53:52,112 --> 00:53:55,604
I heard about somebody
called the Engineer.

526
00:53:55,682 --> 00:53:57,673
I always thought
it was just a...

527
00:53:57,751 --> 00:54:01,983
some campfire story to scare
academy cadets and rookies.

528
00:54:02,055 --> 00:54:04,421
And then today,

529
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:07,551
I heard his name again.

530
00:54:09,829 --> 00:54:12,821
You know what I'm
talking about?

531
00:54:12,899 --> 00:54:16,426
- Oh, please, continue what you were...
- Answer my question!

532
00:54:18,238 --> 00:54:20,832
What do you know
about the Engineer?

533
00:54:52,105 --> 00:54:55,768
I've returned to this file
many times.

534
00:54:55,842 --> 00:54:59,209
It was 1986, my first year
as department counselor.

535
00:55:01,014 --> 00:55:03,983
He was a veteran like you,
good at his job.

536
00:55:04,050 --> 00:55:06,883
Until he caught a case
where everything led to one man...

537
00:55:06,953 --> 00:55:10,480
known only by his street name,
the Engineer.

538
00:55:10,557 --> 00:55:14,653
This detective began
to mistrust his own instincts.

539
00:55:16,229 --> 00:55:18,459
Self-doubt grew
into paranoia.

540
00:55:18,531 --> 00:55:20,897
<i>And in his delusions,</i>

541
00:55:20,967 --> 00:55:24,266
<i>he elevated the Engineer into a figure</i>
<i>of almost supernatural power. </i>

542
00:55:24,337 --> 00:55:28,535
He said the Engineer knew everything
about every cop on the force,

543
00:55:28,608 --> 00:55:31,168
<i>especially him. </i>

544
00:55:31,244 --> 00:55:34,509
His anxiety rapidly shifted
into a deep depression...

545
00:55:35,982 --> 00:55:39,679
till one day he came to work,
sat down behind his desk...

546
00:55:41,021 --> 00:55:42,955
and shot himself
in the head.

547
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:49,456
What do you see there?

548
00:55:49,529 --> 00:55:53,124
The detective had it with him
when he shot himself.

549
00:55:53,199 --> 00:55:57,067
I must admit that I was intrigued
enough to actually go and look for it,

550
00:55:57,137 --> 00:55:59,537
<i>but when I checked</i>
<i>the evidence archives,</i>

551
00:55:59,606 --> 00:56:01,699
