552
00:56:01,775 --> 00:56:04,369
So it's probably either lost
or destroyed by now.

553
00:56:04,444 --> 00:56:07,311
<i>All that's left of it</i>
<i>is the picture. </i>

554
00:56:15,622 --> 00:56:17,419
What is it?

555
00:56:17,490 --> 00:56:21,722
<i>You couldn't get it out of your head. </i>
<i>I think you know. </i>

556
00:56:23,663 --> 00:56:26,325
You're right.
I did some research.

557
00:56:27,834 --> 00:56:30,394
It's called
the Lament Configuration.

558
00:56:32,172 --> 00:56:35,266
It appears in occult literature here
and there throughout the centuries.

559
00:56:35,341 --> 00:56:37,332
What do they say about it?

560
00:56:37,410 --> 00:56:41,346
<i>They say it's a window</i>
<i>or a gateway. </i>

561
00:56:41,414 --> 00:56:43,348
You open it,

562
00:56:43,416 --> 00:56:47,011
they come for you
and they tear you apart.

563
00:56:49,689 --> 00:56:51,623
"They"?

564
00:56:51,691 --> 00:56:55,957
Some call them Cenobites. Others call
them demons and say they take you to hell.

565
00:56:56,029 --> 00:56:59,055
Well, they didn't
take me to hell.

566
00:57:02,035 --> 00:57:05,402
- You opened the box?
- <i>Yeah, last night. </i>

567
00:57:06,473 --> 00:57:09,874
I had some... nightmare,

568
00:57:09,943 --> 00:57:12,207
and...

569
00:57:12,278 --> 00:57:14,212
ever since then,

570
00:57:14,280 --> 00:57:16,475
I've been seeing...

571
00:57:17,784 --> 00:57:19,718
them.

572
00:57:22,655 --> 00:57:26,819
Am I going crazy?

573
00:57:28,561 --> 00:57:32,327
I'm more of a psychiatrist
than I am a priest.

574
00:57:32,398 --> 00:57:36,425
Ask me if I believe in the devil,
I don't know what to say.

575
00:57:36,503 --> 00:57:39,267
But ask me about this box,

576
00:57:39,339 --> 00:57:41,671
from what I've seen
and read,

577
00:57:41,741 --> 00:57:43,675
I believe it's real.

578
00:57:43,743 --> 00:57:46,974
<i>But the history's</i>
<i>consistent. </i>

579
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:50,174
It opens,
they come for you...

580
00:57:50,250 --> 00:57:52,184
and they leave.

581
00:57:52,252 --> 00:57:55,415
<i>So if you're saying</i>
<i>they left you behind,</i>

582
00:57:55,488 --> 00:57:58,514
and you're still seeing them,

583
00:57:58,591 --> 00:58:00,786
then maybe
they're still here.

584
00:58:09,102 --> 00:58:11,468
<i>I live in a world of facts,</i>

585
00:58:11,538 --> 00:58:13,802
<i>of close attention</i>
<i>to detail. </i>

586
00:58:13,873 --> 00:58:16,137
<i>No matter how confusing</i>
<i>the mystery,</i>

587
00:58:16,209 --> 00:58:18,507
<i>no matter how difficult</i>
<i>the puzzle,</i>

588
00:58:18,578 --> 00:58:23,208
<i>the answer is always seen</i>
<i>and the end is natural as rain. </i>

589
00:58:23,283 --> 00:58:27,151
<i>Everything... every process,</i>
<i>no matter how complex,</i>

590
00:58:27,220 --> 00:58:29,484
<i>is a piece of reality</i>
<i>in the end. </i>

591
00:58:29,556 --> 00:58:32,389
<i>And the design</i>
<i>can be understood. </i>

592
00:58:32,458 --> 00:58:36,053
<i>All things can eventually</i>
<i>be explained. </i>

593
00:58:36,129 --> 00:58:40,225
<i>But maybe some facts</i>
<i>are in the eye of the beholder. </i>

594
00:58:40,300 --> 00:58:42,234
Mommy, wait!

595
00:58:42,302 --> 00:58:46,466
<i>And maybe some explanations</i>
