Tell him about the Engineer?

692
01:10:29,407 --> 01:10:32,171
He's not gonna believe my story
until I can prove...

693
01:10:32,243 --> 01:10:34,507
that the Engineer
is the connection!

694
01:10:34,579 --> 01:10:38,174
He's not the fuckin' connection, Joe!
You're the fuckin' connection!

695
01:10:38,249 --> 01:10:41,810
<i>You knew Daphne,</i>
<i>Bernie and Jay Cho. </i>

696
01:10:41,886 --> 01:10:43,820
There is no Engineer.

697
01:10:45,924 --> 01:10:48,449
There's just you.

698
01:10:59,304 --> 01:11:01,534
- Son of a...
- <i>Get up!</i>

699
01:11:01,606 --> 01:11:03,540
Bitch.

700
01:11:03,608 --> 01:11:06,475
You really think
I could kill those people?

701
01:11:06,544 --> 01:11:08,478
You really think
I could do that?

702
01:11:08,546 --> 01:11:11,140
You were with the girl,
you knew about Bernie...

703
01:11:11,215 --> 01:11:15,447
and there was nothin' on the goddamn videotape,
and you knew where to find the finger.

704
01:11:15,520 --> 01:11:17,954
What am I supposed
to think, huh?

705
01:11:19,591 --> 01:11:22,651
Come on, man. I didn't mean
to do that. Now, come on.

706
01:11:24,729 --> 01:11:28,165
Do you really think
I could do those things?

707
01:11:28,232 --> 01:11:30,166
<i>I don't know,</i>
<i> Joseph. </i>

708
01:11:30,234 --> 01:11:33,863
You ask me yesterday, I-I'd say,
"No fuckin' way," but today,

709
01:11:33,938 --> 01:11:36,907
<i>I just don't know. </i>

710
01:11:42,947 --> 01:11:44,881
You need help, Joe.

711
01:11:44,949 --> 01:11:46,883
Go to hell.

712
01:13:42,600 --> 01:13:45,160
<i>Tony?</i>

713
01:13:45,236 --> 01:13:47,170
<i>No. </i>

714
01:14:24,776 --> 01:14:27,040
Six fingers,

715
01:14:27,111 --> 01:14:29,045
six murders.

716
01:14:30,681 --> 01:14:33,206
Only four
fingers left.

717
01:14:40,358 --> 01:14:42,792
Do you know who I am,
Detective?

718
01:14:43,861 --> 01:14:47,888
Oh, let me guess.

719
01:14:47,965 --> 01:14:49,956
You're the Engineer.

720
01:14:52,804 --> 01:14:54,738
I got your message,

721
01:14:54,806 --> 01:14:57,240
and I understand
your fucking game.

722
01:14:58,709 --> 01:15:00,973
Is the child
even alive?

723
01:15:07,218 --> 01:15:09,880
What do you want
from me?

724
01:15:09,954 --> 01:15:12,684
I want you to go home,
Detective.

725
01:15:12,757 --> 01:15:14,748
Time to go home.

726
01:15:17,461 --> 01:15:19,861
We have an officer down.

727
01:15:19,931 --> 01:15:22,263
Mountain Vista
Elementary School.

728
01:15:22,333 --> 01:15:24,597
I don't know the address.
I'm not at the scene.

729
01:15:24,669 --> 01:15:28,036
Just get a unit there
immediately. Out.

730
01:16:18,122 --> 01:16:20,716
<i>Welcome home,</i>
<i>Detective. </i>

731
01:16:25,463 --> 01:16:28,660
<i>It takes hours</i>
<i>to die from exposure. </i>

732
01:16:28,733 --> 01:16:31,395
<i>Hours in which</i>
<i>no one came home. </i>

733
01:16:32,470 --> 01:16:35,234
No one was here
to hear them cry.

734
01:16:38,309 --> 01:16:41,642
<i>Why do you keep</i>
<i>lying to me, Joseph?</i>

735
01:16:41,712 --> 01:16:43,839
You can't
keep doing this.

736
01:16:43,915 --> 01:16:47,544
<i>Daddy?</i>
<i>Are you home?</i>

737
01:16:51,722 --> 01:16:56,182
Yes, baby, Daddy's home.
He's here.

738
01:16:56,260 --> 01:16:58,194
I miss you, Daddy.

739
01:16:58,262 --> 01:17:00,594
When are you
coming home?

740
01:18:05,062 --> 01:18:06,996
They found Tony.

741
01:18:07,064 --> 01:18:11,626
<i>And the child's finger,</i>
<i>the one the killer left in his mouth. </i>

742
01:18:11,702 --> 01:18:13,966
<i>Only this time</i>
<i>the print wasn't burned off. </i>

743
01:18:14,038 --> 01:18:17,030
They ran the print
taken from the severed finger...

744
01:18:17,108 --> 01:18:22,011
and like a miracle,
got a match almost instantly.

745
01:18:22,079 --> 01:18:25,913
<i>What they found doesn't make</i>
<i>any sense though, Joseph,</i>

746
01:18:25,983 --> 01:18:29,111
because the child's
fingerprint...

747
01:18:29,186 --> 01:18:31,120
Well, it's yours.

748
01:18:33,691 --> 01:18:35,818
I don't understand.

749
01:18:37,862 --> 01:18:39,921
I know.

750
01:18:39,997 --> 01:18:42,989
You even misunderstood me
when I told you to go home.

751
01:18:43,067 --> 01:18:45,001
I didn't mean
this place.

752
01:18:46,604 --> 01:18:48,538
I meant
your first home.

753
01:18:48,606 --> 01:18:50,870
<i>The home you grew up in. </i>

754
01:18:52,009 --> 01:18:53,943
<i>I can help you</i>
<i>understand. </i>

755
01:18:54,011 --> 01:18:57,447
You see, I know everything
about you, Joseph.

756
01:19:01,218 --> 01:19:03,152
Your file's
almost complete.

757
01:19:21,305 --> 01:19:23,569
You're the Engineer.

758
01:19:26,710 --> 01:19:29,144
It's as good a name as any.

759
01:19:55,673 --> 01:19:57,607
What are you?

760
01:19:57,675 --> 01:20:02,942
What I am, who I am,
is no concern of yours.

761
01:20:04,982 --> 01:20:07,746
I am not
the killer.

762
01:20:07,818 --> 01:20:09,752
To find him,

763
01:20:09,820 --> 01:20:12,584
you must go back to the place
from which you started.

764
01:20:12,656 --> 01:20:15,181
<i>Go back, Joseph. </i>

765
01:20:15,259 --> 01:20:18,160
Go home.

766
01:21:21,926 --> 01:21:26,295
<i> Joseph? Joseph Thorne?</i>

767
01:22:07,738 --> 01:22:09,672
Dad?

768
01:22:25,689 --> 01:22:28,817
<i>I made brownies, Joseph, your favorite. </i>

769
01:22:46,010 --> 01:22:48,444
<i>You know why</i>
<i>I baked you brownies, Joe?</i>

770
01:22:48,512 --> 01:22:50,571
<i>'Cause you're</i>
<i>such a good boy. </i>

771
01:23:02,359 --> 01:23:05,658
I love you,
Joseph.

772
01:23:05,729 --> 01:23:10,393
We'll save some of these for your father
for when he wakes up from his nap.

773
01:23:16,874 --> 01:23:18,808
Mom?

774
01:24:09,593 --> 01:24:11,993
<i>Why don't you</i>
<i>visit us, Joe?</i>

775
01:24:12,062 --> 01:24:14,530
We never
see you anymore.

776
01:24:14,598 --> 01:24:17,624
- We don't like it here.
- Mom?

777
01:24:20,704 --> 01:24:22,171
Stop!

778
01:24:34,017 --> 01:24:35,951
Dad?

779
01:25:31,308 --> 01:25:33,276
Whatever you want,

780
01:25:33,343 --> 01:25:35,334
as many times
as you want it.

781
01:25:49,593 --> 01:25:52,585
<i>Help me!</i>

782
01:26:09,613 --> 01:26:11,547
I trusted you.

783
01:26:12,683 --> 01:26:14,810
Tony, I'm sorry.

784
01:26:19,423 --> 01:26:21,357
Tony, stop!

785
01:26:28,999 --> 01:26:31,058
I trusted you!

786
01:27:04,368 --> 01:27:07,462
That ain't right,
you treating me like this, Joe.

787
01:27:07,538 --> 01:27:11,440
<i>Bernie?</i>
<i>I'm sorry. I never</i>...

788
01:27:11,508 --> 01:27:14,033
What am I,
your whipping boy?

789
01:27:26,123 --> 01:27:28,455
<i>Help me!</i>

790
01:29:25,308 --> 01:29:27,242
You.

791
01:29:57,541 --> 01:30:00,271
Why?

792
01:30:02,846 --> 01:30:05,872
<i>It's all a puzzle, isn't it, Joseph?</i>

793
01:30:05,949 --> 01:30:08,213
<i>Like a game of chess,</i>
<i>perhaps. </i>

794
01:30:08,285 --> 01:30:10,913
The pieces move,
apparently aimlessly,

795
01:30:10,987 --> 01:30:15,083
but always towards
one single objective:

796
01:30:15,158 --> 01:30:18,252
To kill the king.

797
01:30:18,328 --> 01:30:21,229
Who is the king
in this game, Joseph?

798
01:30:21,298 --> 01:30:24,961
<i>That is the question</i>
<i>you must ask yourself. </i>

799
01:30:25,035 --> 01:30:28,835
Don't you recognize
your own flesh,

800
01:30:28,905 --> 01:30:31,806
your own spirit?

801
01:30:33,310 --> 01:30:35,744
I don't understand.

802
01:30:38,014 --> 01:30:40,983
the eternal refrain
of humanity...

803
01:30:41,051 --> 01:30:44,043
pleading ignorance,
begging for mercy.

804
01:30:44,121 --> 01:30:47,750
"Please, help me.
I don't understand. "

805
01:30:47,824 --> 01:30:51,885
<i>This is the life</i>
<i>you chose, Joseph. </i>

806
01:30:51,962 --> 01:30:53,896
<i>All the people</i>
<i>you hurt,</i>

807
01:30:53,964 --> 01:30:56,330
all the appetites
you indulged.

808
01:30:56,399 --> 01:30:59,562
<i>You have destroyed</i>
<i>your own innocence,</i>

809
01:30:59,636 --> 01:31:03,663
allowed your flesh
to consume your spirit.

810
01:31:05,242 --> 01:31:07,870
You are your own king,

811
01:31:07,944 --> 01:31:12,643
and this is the hell you
have created for yourself.

812
01:31:19,523 --> 01:31:21,457
No.

813
01:31:29,466 --> 01:31:33,129
Your flesh
is killing your spirit.

814
01:31:33,203 --> 01:31:36,366
No!

815
01:31:37,641 --> 01:31:39,871
Oh, yes, Joseph.

816
01:31:42,579 --> 01:31:45,275
You have forsaken
yourself.

817
01:31:56,760 --> 01:31:59,456
Only one finger
left now, Joseph.

818
01:32:00,597 --> 01:32:03,589
<i>Only one more</i>
<i>death to go. </i>

819
01:32:22,385 --> 01:32:25,115
Welcome to hell.

820
01:33:25,849 --> 01:33:28,613
Jesus. Haven't I
earned my money yet?

821
01:33:30,520 --> 01:33:32,454
I'm sorry.

822
01:34:12,629 --> 01:34:15,757
- <i>How'd you do?</i>
- What?

823
01:34:15,832 --> 01:34:18,426
The game last night. How'd you do?

824
01:34:18,501 --> 01:34:20,526
Well, we...

825
01:34:20,603 --> 01:34:23,800
We won by seven,
but it should've been 20.

826
01:34:23,873 --> 01:34:25,807
<i>Tony no-showed. </i>

827
01:34:25,875 --> 01:34:27,809
I had to go fishin'.

828
01:34:31,948 --> 01:34:33,973
Detective Thorne.

829
01:34:36,553 --> 01:34:39,454
Hey, Joe, it's Daphne.

830
01:34:39,522 --> 01:34:42,787
I'm the girl
you were with last night.

831
01:34:42,859 --> 01:34:46,090
Please!
I'm still at the motel.

832
01:34:46,162 --> 01:34:48,960
Oh, my God.
Oh, God.

833
01:34:49,032 --> 01:34:51,728
What's the matter, Joe?
You okay?

834
01:34:57,574 --> 01:34:59,565
No, don't do it!

835
01:35:19,396 --> 01:35:21,830
<i>I lived in a world of facts,</i>

836
01:35:21,898 --> 01:35:25,629
<i>of a reality that</i>
<i>I thought I understood. </i>

837
01:35:25,702 --> 01:35:28,296
<i>I believed I was</i>
<i>the center of the design... </i>

838
01:35:28,371 --> 01:35:31,135
<i>and I was certain</i>
<i>that I knew all the answers. </i>

839
01:35:32,976 --> 01:35:36,912
<i>But now I face the truth about</i>
<i>what I've done to hurt those around me,</i>

840
01:35:36,980 --> 01:35:40,916
<i>and in hurting them,</i>
<i>what I've done to myself. </i>

841
01:35:44,054 --> 01:35:46,750
<i>I've confronted</i>
<i>my own demons,</i>

842
01:35:46,823 --> 01:35:50,224
<i>and now the only thing</i>
<i>I know for certain... </i>

843
01:35:50,293 --> 01:35:52,818
<i>is that I will</i>
<i>live with them forever. </i>

844
01:35:55,698 --> 01:35:57,962
No!

845
01:35:59,936 --> 01:36:03,372
<i> ¤ Dreamed a world ¤</i>

846
01:36:03,440 --> 01:36:05,101
<i> ¤ Of lies ¤</i>

847
01:36:11,114 --> 01:36:15,881
<i> ¤ Safe as milk ¤</i>

848
01:36:17,487 --> 01:36:21,753
<i> ¤ With clouded eyes ¤</i>

849
01:36:22,826 --> 01:36:27,195
<i> ¤ Pure is your soul ¤</i>

850
01:36:28,298 --> 01:36:32,632
<i> ¤ The trust that we stole ¤</i>

851
01:36:32,702 --> 01:36:38,402
<i> ¤ From each other ¤</i>

852
01:37:02,765 --> 01:37:06,633
<i> ¤ Underneath the bed ¤</i>

853
01:37:06,703 --> 01:37:09,399
<i> ¤ At night ¤</i>

854
01:37:14,244 --> 01:37:18,271
<i> ¤ Truth ends up wrong ¤</i>

855
01:37:18,348 --> 01:37:24,048
<i> ¤ And right ¤</i>

856
01:37:26,022 --> 01:37:31,460
<i> ¤ Dyin'to stay ¤</i>

857
01:37:31,528 --> 01:37:35,862
<i> ¤ We're runnin'away ¤</i>

858
01:37:35,932 --> 01:37:41,268
<i> ¤ From Eden ¤</i>

859
01:38:16,773 --> 01:38:40,185
<i> ¤ We're livin'in the best</i>
<i>of all possible worlds ¤</i>

